@Node BBSArt_Using
@{u}BBSArt Using@{uu}

   Click on the tools in the window on the right hand side then draw on the
screen its that simple.

   @{b}Here is description of what each tools does:@{ub}



   F1 - F9     ANSIsets 1-9            F10 - toolspanel  on/off

   *Not implemented yet                  **Not FULLY implemented yet
                               ________
                              | Coords |<---- X, Y Coords
                              |        |
           Freehand drawing-->|  Draw  |
                              |   Box  |<-- Unfilled box (using current pen)
            Filled box------->|Fill Box|
**Border Box                  |  Line  |<---- Line *
  (using @current border set)>|Bord Box|
                              |BordLine|<--- line using current horizontal
                              |        |          or vertical @border char *
                              |FGColour|<-- foreground colour select
  BackGround colour select -->|BGColour|

                     PP=Current ASCII character pen
  FF=Foreground colour   >    |FF PP BB| < BB=Background colour

                               ...ASC Pallette

  ANSI Palette selector ----> @{u}| < 01 > |@{uu}

@Endnode

@Node BBSArt_Work
@{u}Work in Progress@{uu}

@{b}09/08/95@{ub}

   I haven't done any work on line (border or current character), this is
waiting for an routine from a friend so I can draw at any angle.  If this
doesn't come thru I'm going to just do diagonals, vert & horizontal lines -
hey I'm a lazy programmer.

   Not all ANSI characters are available thru the palette & I haven't done
any work on keyboard entry to the screen.

   Cut and paste will be available soon & I'm doing rectangluar selection, I
might make it so you can save out 'brushes'.

   I'm not right happy with the response on the function keys but it seems
to work ok with my A1200 + 2Mb fast ram.  The function keys are read by
peeking directly on address &HBFEC01! bypassing the OS not Ideal but it
works :).

